    "recap_headline": "California State University Northridge Athletics",
    "recap_text": "FULLERTON, Calif.\n---Behind five home runs and another standout performance on the mound, CSUN Baseball clinched a series win with a 5-3 decision at Cal State Fullerton on Saturday at Goodwin Field.\nMatthew Thomas\nfinished with three hits including a towering solo home run while\nTraig Oughton\nworked seven quality innings with two runs allowed and eight strikeouts in the victory.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nFor the second consecutive day, the Matadors struck first in the first inning against Fullerton pitching. CSUN took advantage of a two-out throwing error off the bat of\nMateo Rickman\nto bring\nMatthew Pena\nto the plate. Pena delivered with an RBI double off the wall in right field for a 1-0 lead.\nCSUN would flex its muscles in the second inning, slugging three solo home runs to extend to a 4-0 advantage.\nWill Linberg\nand\nMatthew Cormier\nhit back-to-back homers to begin the frame while\nKyle Panganiban\nlater hit a two-out solo homer to knock starting pitcher Dylan Smith out of the game.\nBACK-2-BACK!\nMatthew Cormier\ngoes deep as well in the 2nd inning to extend the lead to 3-0!\n#GoMatadors\npic.twitter.com/8ccaYSAaM0\n\u2014 CSUN Baseball (@CSUNBaseball)\nMarch 22, 2026\nOn the flip side, Oughton baffled Titan hitters throughout the night. The right hander scattered five hits over his seven innings of work with the only blemish coming in the third inning.\nThe Titans pushed across two runs in the third inning on two-out hits from Paul Contreras and Nick Miller before Oughton retired Andrew Kirchner to finally end the threat.\nOughton retired seven of eight batters after giving up the two runs in the third, keeping the Matadors in front. He then racked up four strikeouts over his last two innings of work before exiting after the bottom of the seventh.\nCSUN added to its lead over the seventh and eighth innings as Thomas and\nVaughn Coleman\nclubbed solo home runs for a 6-2 lead.\nMatthew Thomas\njoining in on the HR derby.\nThomas hammers a no doubter to left for his 9th of the season. CSUN leads 5-2 in the 7th.\n#GoMatadors\npic.twitter.com/CgpKwZnXQU\n\u2014 CSUN Baseball (@CSUNBaseball)\nMarch 22, 2026\nFullerton threatened once more in the eighth against Matador reliever\nLogan Miller\n, picking up consecutive singles to start the frame. However, Miller retired the next three batters in succession to end the threat.\nJaiden Turner\ntook over in the ninth on the mound, retiring three of four batters to nail down the win.\nNOTES OF THE GAME\nCSUN improves to 13-9 overall and 4-4 in Big West play while Cal State Fullerton drops to 10-12 overall and 5-3 in conference.\nOughton's eight strikeouts and seven innings pitched set new season highs. He also improved to 3-0 on the year.\nThomas recorded his team-high eighth multiple-hit game of the season.\nColton Boardman\nfinished 1-for-4 to extend his hit streak to eight games.\nBoth Pena and Linberg stretched their respective on base streaks to eight games.\nCSUN has now won three straight series at Cal State Fullerton, dating back to 2022.\nACCORDING TO COACH EDDIE CORNEJO\n\"We did a great job of hitting mistakes today and capitalized on them. We didn't get rewarded last Saturday for quality swings but today we did, that's baseball.\nTraig Oughton\ndeserves to be recognized for his 111-pitch performance. He finished strong and kept us in it for the big swings to make a difference.\"\nUP NEXT\nCSUN looks for a series sweep on Sunday when the Matadors take on Cal State Fullerton at 1 p.m. on ESPN+.\n#GoMatadors",
